Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.50,0:00:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\b0}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,1440)}在过去的六千年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the last 6,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.54,0:00:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,1440)}地球的表面发生了突然的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the surface of our planet has undergone a sudden change.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.88,0:00:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个新的栖息地已经出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A new habitat has appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.42,0:00:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全人为设计和建造的这个景观\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}entirely designed and constructed by one species for its own purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.81,0:01:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许会对动物的生命造成威胁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This man-made landscape may seem alien to animal life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.77,0:01:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但对于勇者来说  这是一个充满奇妙机遇的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but for the bold, this is a world of surprising opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,100)\fs150\t(,\fs280)\bord0\b0\pos(960,1100)}城        市
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.89,0:01:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,印度焦特布尔市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Jodhpur, India.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.48,0:01:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群单身的雄性长尾叶猴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A gang of bachelor male langurs
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.24,0:01:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前来挑战这块领地的雄性首领\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has come to challenge the resident alpha male.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.49,0:01:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他统治着这片珍贵的城市领土\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This alpha rules over a valuable urban territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.38,0:01:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但维护权威是一场长期的斗争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But maintaining dominance here is a constant struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.76,0:02:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,单身雄猴们联合起来试图推翻猴王\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bachelors have united to try and overthrow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.23,0:02:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他们胜利了  其中一位挑战者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If they win, one of the challengers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.98,0:02:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将继承猴王的后宫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will take over the alpha's troop of females,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.11,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并杀死他的幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and may kill his infants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.45,0:02:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个单身猴群里有十五只公猴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are 15 males in this bachelor group.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猴王必须把他们全部逐出自己的领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The alpha must evict every single one of them from his territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.93,0:02:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经赶走了半数挑战者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He has chased half the bachelors away,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.14,0:03:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有一支小分队折了回来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but a splinter group has looped back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.22,0:03:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正在骚扰他的母猴们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and is harassing his females.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.57,0:03:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不得不再次加入战斗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once again, he has to battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.27,0:03:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终于赶走了所有来犯者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Finally, he manages to expel them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.65,0:03:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他凯旋而归\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He returns home victorious,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:04:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但右腿受了重伤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but with a serious wound on his right leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.41,0:04:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他而言  城市生活布满荆棘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a hard life for him in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天都上演着入侵驱逐战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Keeping the intruders away is a daily challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但一切都值得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it's worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.47,0:04:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对长尾叶猴来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For these urban territories
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.26,0:04:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边城区也许是世上最优良的栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are probably the best langur territories in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.73,0:04:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为遍地都是觅食场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're filled with rich feeding grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这些寺院花园中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here in the temple gardens,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.32,0:04:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几百年来  长尾叶猴与人类建立了一种奇妙的关系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the langurs have, over centuries, developed a surprising relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这层关系为猴群提供了源源不断的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One that guarantee's them a constantly replenished source of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当地人将长尾叶猴视为印度教中猴神哈奴曼的化身\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The people here associate langurs with the Hindu God, Lord Hanuman,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他们毕恭毕敬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and revere them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.53,0:05:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,珍馐佳肴  应有尽有\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're given all the food they can eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.62,0:05:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,优质饮食带来了生育高峰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this high-energy diet has led to a baby boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.01,0:05:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市里雌性长尾叶猴的生育率\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Female langurs in this city
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.51,0:05:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是森林中同类的两倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}give birth to twice as many young as their forest counterparts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.77,0:06:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只母猴伙食很好  奶水充足到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This mother is so well fed that her rich milk
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.10,0:06:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能养育起野外极其罕见的小生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can support something rarely seen in the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双胞胎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.82,0:06:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些幼崽聚集成群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And all these babies can create troops
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,队伍比周边森林里的要大得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that are far larger than those found in the forests nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.62,0:06:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,觅食时间缩短  使得他们有更多时间可以玩耍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With less time spent looking for food,there is more time for play.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生活在城市中好处良多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rewards of living in a city can be huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难的是如何寻找自己的一席之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The challenge is to find your niche.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.21,0:06:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样一个世界  并不是专为野生动物的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But how to create a home in a world that wasn't designed for wildlife?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:07:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,灯光  声音和忙碌超过任何地方的自然世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's far brighter, louder and busier than anywhere in the natural world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,持续的交通造成了动物运动的障碍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The continuous traffic creates barriers to animal movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.77,0:07:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今后十年  城市面积预计将\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And in this decade,the urban environment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,扩张约百分之三十\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is predicted to grow by nearly 30%.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.36,0:07:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更重要的是  来这里的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What's more, to come here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.11,0:07:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物必须与世界顶级捕食者竞争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}animals have to compete with the world's top predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们建立了这里的规则\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}People makes the rules here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四十亿人口现在居住在城市环境中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Four billion human beings now live in the urban environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里  动物必须抗争最大的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's here that animals have to contend with the greatest change
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.81,0:07:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生在我们的星球\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that is happenning to the face our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.39,0:08:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以为什么会有动物想来这里呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So why would any animal want to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纽约市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座高楼林立的城市  与地球上许多地方一样远离自然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This densely built-up landscape is as unnatural as anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.99,0:08:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这只游隼正站在高处  俯瞰这座城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And yet this wild peregrine falcon looks out onto an ideal habitat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奇怪的是  这片变化巨大的土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Strange as it may seem, this vastly-altered landscape
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,竟然重现了游隼进化的生境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}replicates the conditions in which peregrines evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.30,0:09:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高耸的建筑上面有许多平台\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The towering buildings have a multitude of ledges
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.22,0:09:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可供游隼筑巢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on which falcons can nest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸟巢高度也足够他们乘风飞翔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the high perches that they need to catch the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纽约市的游隼密度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}New York City has the highest density
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,居世界之最\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of nesting peregrines anywhere on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,风被摩天大楼阻挡后会向上偏转\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Winds striking the sides of the skyscrapers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有利于游隼飞得更高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are deflected upwards and can help the birds gain height.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.59,0:09:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,烈日下大面积的混凝土散发的热量形成上升热气流\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the great areas of concrete roasting in the sun create thermals,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.39,0:09:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游隼不费吹灰之力便可以在城市上空翱翔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so that, with very little effort， the birds can soar over the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.82,0:10:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不计其数的游隼定居于此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And so many peregrines can live here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.74,0:10:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为城市近地面生活着许多猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because down at street level, there is a lot of potential prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.92,0:10:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游隼俯冲时的飞行时速\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Diving from height, the falcons can reach speeds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.97,0:10:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,超过时速三百二十二公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of over 200 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.39,0:10:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但猎物躲在低处  离建筑物很近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But their prey stay down low and close to the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.61,0:10:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,风险太大了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.94,0:10:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它停止了俯冲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The peregrine pulls out of his stoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:10:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但辛苦不会白费\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the effort is not wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游隼需要将猎物驱赶到开阔地带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The falcons need to flush their prey into the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曼哈顿四面环水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And Manhattan is surrounded by water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.80,0:11:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出城后便可谓胜券在握\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out here the odds change.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正中游隼下怀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And in the peregrine's favour.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一年到头都有着丰富的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With abundant prey here all year round,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.98,0:12:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅用了四十年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it has taken only 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.69,0:12:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游隼在此建立栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for these falcons to establish themselves here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿梭在摩登大厦中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And now, among skyscrapers, they're more successful
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.20,0:12:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与旷野中的同类相比  它们更胜一筹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}than their cousins living in the wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.00,0:12:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,印度孟买人口超过两千万\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mumbai, in India, is home to over 20 million people..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.63,0:12:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也生存着许多猎食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And there are predators here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.38,0:12:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管难得一见  也着实令人胆战心惊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that, though rarely seen, are rightly feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,食肉动物们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Carnivores,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正向着毫无戒心的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}lured by the prospect of plentiful unsuspecting prey
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一步步靠近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are on the prowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只金钱豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A leopard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在夜色的掩护下  他们每晚都会出来猎食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every night, under the cover of darkness they come out to hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.83,0:13:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大型食肉动物需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are big animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寻找大型猎物才能充饥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're looking for large prey to satisfy their hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.89,0:13:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了多捕捉一些画面揭示他们的猎食行为\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To catch more than a glimpse of them and reveal their hunting behaviour,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.06,0:13:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要夜视摄像机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}you need night-vision cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的二十五年里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Leopards have attacked almost 200 people here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.62,0:14:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金钱豹袭击过约两百个人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in the last 25 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.93,0:14:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但人类并不是他们日常的捕食对象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But humans are not their usual prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.06,0:14:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些金钱豹在寻找其他猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These leopards are on the hunt for something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们更喜欢人类圈养在城市里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These leopards prefer to hunt the domestic animals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数量可观的家畜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that people have brought to the city in considerable numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猪喜欢群居\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The pigs keep their family close.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市里无休止的嘈杂为金钱豹提供了便利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ceaseless noise of the city plays to their advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.14,0:16:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,掩盖了他们的脚步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It conceals their approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.06,0:16:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金钱豹利用掩护能在全城各地捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the leopards are using this cover to hunt all over the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.21,0:16:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个种群日益繁荣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a thriving population.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.30,0:16:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上  世界上金钱豹数量最多的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In fact, the highest concentration of leopards in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.34,0:16:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.77,0:16:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,充足的食物并不是吸引野生动物迁入城市的唯一要素\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not only the abundance of food that attracts wild animals to cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.82,0:17:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市的气温通常比郊外略高几度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're usually several degrees warmer than the surrounding countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.70,0:17:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十二月的罗马\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And here in Rome, in Decembe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.70,0:17:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一种动物充分利用着这丝温暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one animal is taking full advantage of this extra heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.71,0:17:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在城市中留下自己的印记\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's leaving it's mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.76,0:17:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冬季的每一天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In a single winter's day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.01,0:17:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都有十吨粪便雨降临这座城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}ten tonnes of its droppings rain down on the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.56,0:17:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欧椋鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Starlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.15,0:17:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜晚  它们在郊外摄食后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the evening, they come back to the warmth of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,返回温暖的城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}after feeding in the neighbouring countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须返回栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They must return to their roosting trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.20,0:17:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但第一个回来的最有可能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the first to do so are at the highest risk
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.49,0:17:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被猛禽袭击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of being caught by birds of prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以它们等候大部队一同抵达\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, they wait for others to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数量越多就越安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's safety in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.38,0:18:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天光渐暗  城市上空被数百万只欧椋鸟占据\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As daylight fades, the sky fills with a staggering one million starlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上演一场蔚然壮观的自然演出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And then follows one of nature's great spectaculars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.60,0:19:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是如何  又是为何成群起舞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}How, or indeed why, they perform these marvellous aerobatics,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.19,0:19:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至今我们还无法完全理解\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we still do not fully understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终  它们会成群结队地降落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eventually, en masse，they brave the descent
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.04,0:19:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挑选最喜欢的树枝落脚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and fill the branches of their favourite trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.67,0:19:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这样寒冷的冬夜里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On these cold winter nights, the city's extra warmth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市的温暖可能事关生死存亡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can mean the difference between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.56,0:20:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市不仅能提供大量食物与庇护所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A city, of course, can provide
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.77,0:20:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有许多宝藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}not only shelter and abundant food, but glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.82,0:20:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些精心挑选的小物件\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These varied objects have been carefully chosen
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,颜色鲜艳  溢彩流光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by a bird for their brightness and their colour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.66,0:20:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只园丁鸟花了十余年时间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This great bowerbird has spent over a decade
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.04,0:20:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收集了这些物品  其中大部分是人造装饰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}building this collection of mostly man-made objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.42,0:20:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,澳大利亚汤斯维尔市的高尔夫球场上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out on a golf course in Townsville, Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.39,0:20:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正在为这座巨型凉亭做最后的修饰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he's putting the final touches to his enormous bower,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,争取能够博得来访雌鸟的青睐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that he hopes will impress a visiting female.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.90,0:20:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他每天都会花两小时来调整装饰物的布局\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He spends two hours each day rearranging his prized objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.07,0:21:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“放在那边可能更好看一点”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"Perhaps that would look a little better over there."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.96,0:21:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可似乎还是差了点什么\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it seems that something is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没有进城去找新装饰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Instead of going into town to collect new objects,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.84,0:21:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是决定抢劫邻居\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he's decided to raid his neighbour's bower.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.39,0:21:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“晾衣夹  太棒了”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"A clothes peg! Excellent!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.73,0:21:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“还有一辆闪亮的玩具车”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"And a shiny toy car."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.44,0:21:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果被发现就不好玩了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a risky game if you get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主人回来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The owner is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一座凉亭  值得去冒险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is one bower where the risk is worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.17,0:21:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一件特别的物品吸引了他的目光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A particular object has caught his eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.42,0:22:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他需要等主人离开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He'll have to wait for the owner to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.40,0:22:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,机会来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is his chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.27,0:22:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是真正的宝贝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A real treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.78,0:22:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,深红色的心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A scarlet heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“拿到了”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"Got it."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,供雌鸟参观的舞台已经准备就绪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The stage is now set for female visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.71,0:22:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他似乎很走运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His luck may be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.39,0:23:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以开始尽情引诱了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The seduction can now begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.90,0:23:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他开始炫耀自己的收藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's showing off his best goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.94,0:23:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“这个塑料管怎么样”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"Perhaps a little plastic piping?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.82,0:23:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“我还有鲜艳的红丝线”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"Or maybe a bit of coloured string?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.29,0:23:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这位访客似乎对此毫无兴趣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But his guest doesn't seem to be paying much attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.84,0:23:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“这把叉子呢”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"A fork?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.38,0:23:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“女士”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}"Madame?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.10,0:23:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对方依旧无动于衷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nothing seems to be working.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.98,0:23:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事情有些不对劲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Something is just not quite right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.19,0:24:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他还有一招\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But he still has one trick up his sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那颗红心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The scarlet heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.89,0:24:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作为压轴节目  他张开了头部后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As a final thrill，he expands the pink crest
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.64,0:24:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,头部后侧的粉色羽冠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.73,0:24:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,证明他已经成年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sign of his adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.36,0:24:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他弄错了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But he's made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.53,0:24:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只不是雌鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is not a female
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.19,0:24:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一只还没有长出羽冠的雄鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but a young male who hasn't yet developed that head crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.70,0:24:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他衔起红心飞走了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And he's making off with the scarlet heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.12,0:24:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在城里求偶着实不易\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not easy finding sex in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.09,0:25:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在城市里养活子女也不轻松\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Raising a family in the city is not easy either.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.17,0:25:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多伦多已经到了春季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's spring time in Toronto,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.47,0:25:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只浣熊妈妈的家  从树顶换成了屋顶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and this mother raccoon has exchanged her native treetops for rooftops.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.94,0:25:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两个月前她产下的幼崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Since giving birth two months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.11,0:25:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被她放在烟囱里  那里温暖又安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}she's kept her offspring safe and warm inside a chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.41,0:25:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在  这些宝宝们住不下了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, her young have outgrown their nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.25,0:25:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是当妈妈的第一个大挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is her first major challenge as a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.29,0:25:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搬新家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The time has come to move to a new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.13,0:25:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她得把孩子们从屋顶带下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She needs to get her youngster to ground level.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.80,0:26:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可脚下不是方便攀爬的树干\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But instead of an easy climb down a tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.06,0:26:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是垂直陡峭的墙壁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}she is faced with a vertical drop,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.23,0:26:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎没有着力点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}with little to cling onto.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.36,0:26:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,浣熊宝宝第一次看到城市世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her baby's first glimpse of the urban world,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.65,0:26:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却是在惊悚的九米高空\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}from a terrifying 30 feet up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.39,0:26:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只浣熊宝宝是最后一个了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the last of her litter to be brought down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.77,0:27:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的兄弟们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its siblings are already
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.48,0:27:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经忙着探索未知世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}busy exploring the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.82,0:27:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要学的还有许多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they have much to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.62,0:27:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只浣熊宝宝掉进后巷  被困在了这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This one has fallen into a back alley and is trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.62,0:27:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈来救它  告诉它应该怎么做\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mother comes to the rescue and demonstrates what must be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.31,0:27:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是这样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That's the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.82,0:27:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,浣熊是一群投机分子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Raccoons are opportunists.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.24,0:27:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十分渴望探索新世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they're eager to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.29,0:28:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们需要尽快学会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they'll have to learn very quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.50,0:28:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如何适应这样一个既陌生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}how to get along in this strange new environment
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又充满危险的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so full of hazards.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.55,0:28:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈再次前来救助\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mother comes to the rescue once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.35,0:28:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市浣熊与乡村浣熊相比\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Urban raccoons are now demonstrably better
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.69,0:28:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拥有更加卓越的问题解决能力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}at problem-solving than their country cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.99,0:28:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,食物来源如此丰富\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When the feeding opportunities are this good,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.53,0:28:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,花点时间想办法获取食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the time spent working out how to get to it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.24,0:28:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也非常值得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is well worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.09,0:28:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,复杂的城市生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The complexity of urban life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.76,0:29:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要智取\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}favours the clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.43,0:29:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是要想在白天与人类竞争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But to compete with humanity during daylight hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.94,0:29:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要的不只是智慧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}takes more than just intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.48,0:29:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有胆量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It takes nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.49,0:29:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群雄心勃勃的猴子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One enterprising species of monkey
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.24,0:29:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搬到了印度斋浦尔市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has moved into the city of Jaipur in India.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.45,0:29:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恒河猕猴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Rhesus macaque.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.79,0:29:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如何拿到这些鲜嫩多汁的水果呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But how to get a share of all this juicy fruit?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.64,0:29:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天早上  猴子军团都会和上班族一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every morning, the troop make the same journey
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.98,0:30:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走同样的路线  穿越城市丛林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}through the urban jungle, just as human commuters do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.71,0:30:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候  难免会遇到交通拥堵\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sometimes, inevitably, there are traffic jams.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.69,0:30:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等他们抵达市场  麻烦就开始了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once they get to the market, trouble begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.67,0:31:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有勇有谋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Being both intelligent and brazen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.01,0:31:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才能在人类的地盘占上风\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is the key to beating human beings on their home turf.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.22,0:32:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简直是光天化日下的抢劫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's daylight robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.27,0:32:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在大多数人看来  生活在城市中的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are some animals that most would consider too dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.94,0:32:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些动物太过危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to tolerate in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.86,0:32:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斑鬣狗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Spotted hyenas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.91,0:32:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们所到之处  其他动物都退避三舍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're feared throughout their range.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.25,0:32:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在埃塞俄比亚哈拉市郊外\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the outskirts of Hara in Ethiopia,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.38,0:32:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两群鬣狗针锋相对  准备争夺宝贵资源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}two clans are coming face to face to battle over a prized resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.10,0:33:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两边队伍各有六十只左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are about 60 hyenas in each clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.48,0:33:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,势均力敌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they're well matched.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.33,0:33:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经过三小时的来回周旋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After three hours of posturing back and forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.46,0:33:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一支队伍败退\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the losers retreat
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.38,0:33:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赢家则出发去享受战果\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the victors head to claim their prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.22,0:33:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们争夺的正是进入城区的权利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have been fighting over access to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.28,0:34:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦穿过城墙  它们就直奔目的地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once inside the city walls，they head for one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.21,0:34:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且也很清楚该如何去那里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they know exactly how to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.74,0:34:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一家历史悠久的肉店\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ancient meat market.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.58,0:35:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物残骸的浓重气息飘散在空气中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The scent of all these carcasses lies heavy in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.48,0:35:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个传统已经持续了四百多年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This tradition goes back over 400 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.07,0:35:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,屠夫们会把不要的骨头扔出来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The human butchers put out the bones they don't need
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.53,0:35:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由这些鬣狗负责处理\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and these hyenas deal with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.20,0:35:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有它们有这个能力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the only animals that can.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.83,0:35:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他动物的咬合力不足以咬断骨头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No other here has such powerful bone-crushing jaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.71,0:35:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类与野兽的这种关系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this relationship between man and beast
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.80,0:35:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今已经发展到了新高度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has now been taken a step further.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.89,0:36:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,约瑟夫在呼唤鬣狗们去他家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yousuf is calling the hyenas to his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.94,0:36:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和他的祖辈  连续五代人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He and his forefathers, going back five generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.86,0:36:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在喂食这些鬣狗时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have been feeding the hyenas
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.28,0:36:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都直接用手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.82,0:36:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,住在这里的市民们认为\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The inhabitants of this town believe that hyenas
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.29,0:36:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鬣狗还有一个非常重要的本事\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}provide another very important service.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.66,0:36:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够吞噬游荡在街道上的恶魂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eating the bad spirits that haunt the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.51,0:36:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种动物凶猛而残暴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are wild and ferocious animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.93,0:36:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是在城区内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but once within these city walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.51,0:36:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们表现出了完全不同的一面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they behave in a completely different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.68,0:36:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在非洲的其他地区  大家都十分惧怕斑鬣狗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Throughout the rest of Africa，spotted hyenas are feared
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.48,0:37:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们猎食家畜  甚至伤及孩童\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because they kill livestock, sometimes even children.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.11,0:37:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斑鬣狗大概是地球上最受诟病的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are perhaps the most vilified animal on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.83,0:37:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而  在哈勒尔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}However, here in Harar,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.95,0:37:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们却能够与人类和平共处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their relationship with people is entirely peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.71,0:37:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赢得了人类的信任\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have won the trust of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.18,0:37:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丧失对人类的恐惧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Losing its fear of humans
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.35,0:37:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让一种动物遍布世界各个城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has enabled one animal to spread into cities everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.35,0:37:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且数量庞大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and in huge numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.07,0:37:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸽子是目前最成功的城市鸟类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pigeons are by far the most successful urban bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.37,0:38:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在法国南部的阿尔比\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, in Albi, in the south of France,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.95,0:38:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸽群飞到河边沐浴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the pigeons come to the river to bathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.42,0:38:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们要整理飞羽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They need to preen their flight feathers,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.29,0:38:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,清洗掉城市的灰尘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}clean off the city dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.13,0:38:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并给自己降降温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and cool themselves down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.69,0:38:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而死神正埋伏以待\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But death lies in wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.32,0:38:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,捕食者正是利用了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A predator that has taken advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.45,0:38:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸽子在城市得以成功生存的法宝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of the very thing that has led to the pigeon's success...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.12,0:38:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们已丧失的恐惧感\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their lack of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.04,0:38:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸽子洗澡时  羽毛上的油脂顺流而下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the pigeons bathe，oil from their plumage flows downstream,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.71,0:39:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被捕食者察觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and is detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.52,0:39:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一条巨大的六须鲶鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A monstrous Wels catfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.52,0:39:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然才被引入此地四十年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Introduced here just 40 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.53,0:39:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,繁殖数量却已大大增长  几乎迫使本地鱼类灭绝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they have proliferated. Virtually exterminated the local fish stocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.66,0:39:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在它们将猎食对象转向了鸽子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they've now developed a taste for pigeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.95,0:39:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于视力微弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their eyesight is poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.83,0:39:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们依靠触须来探测猎物的动静\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so they use their barbels to sense the movements of their victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.05,0:40:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对底栖鱼类来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is a radical new hunting strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.14,0:40:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是种全新的捕猎策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for what is normally a bottom-dwelling fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.86,0:41:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在城市居住了上千年之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After a thousand years of living in this city,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.83,0:41:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸽子现在却要学会避开水里的鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}pigeons are now having to learn to avoid a fish
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.34,0:41:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的城市在不断变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Our cities are always changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.09,0:41:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时极为迅速\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sometimes very swiftly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.63,0:41:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物们必须应对这些改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And animals must cope with the changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.05,0:41:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则就会消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.60,0:41:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,近年来  最大的变化之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One of the greatest changes in recent times
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.81,0:41:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是由一项历史还不到一百四十年的发明引起的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has come from a single invention made less than 140 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.99,0:41:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,电灯\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Electric light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.82,0:41:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的影响力越来越大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has become more and more powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.91,0:41:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,点亮了我们的街道\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}filling our streets with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.22,0:42:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市灯光无处不在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's everywhere in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.34,0:42:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至延伸到地下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It even goes under ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.24,0:42:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白天与黑夜的区别愈发难以分辨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The difference between day and night is becoming less and less perceptible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.38,0:42:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这对野生动物产生了深远的影响\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And that has a profound effect on the activities of wildlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.39,0:43:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在野外  光引发动物的各种行为\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the wilderness, light triggers all kinds of behaviour.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.27,0:43:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在月圆之夜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On the night of the full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.15,0:43:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数百只刚孵化的小玳瑁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}hundreds of tiny hawksbill turtle hatchlings
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.28,0:43:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从安全的沙底洞穴中钻出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}emerge from the safety of their nest deep in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.86,0:43:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本能驱使它们尽快爬到海里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their instinct is to reach the sea as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.12,0:43:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,指引它们方向的是海水倒映的月光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And their guide is the light of the full moon reflected on the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.51,0:43:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这只小玳瑁感到很困惑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this young hatchling is confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.18,0:43:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它正朝错误的方向爬去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's going in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.28,0:44:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明亮的灯光从陆地照来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bright light is coming from the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.07,0:44:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让这些小玳瑁都从沙滩爬向内陆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And all these hatchlings are travelling up the beach towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.04,0:44:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,捕食者伺机而动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Predators are ready to take advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.09,0:44:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,螃蟹将巢穴直接建在沙滩灯光下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Crabs now make their burrows directly beneath the beach lights
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.97,0:44:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等猎物自己送上门\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and wait for their prey to come to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.66,0:44:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使能成功逃脱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even if a hatchling escapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.91,0:44:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们仍身处险境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they're still in peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.50,0:45:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,灯光愈发具有迷惑性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The lights become more and more bewildering.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.82,0:45:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片沙滩上百分之八十的小玳瑁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}80% of all hatchlings on this beach
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.15,0:45:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都因城市的灯光而迷失了方向\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are now disorientated by the lights of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.22,0:46:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多小生命终结了在马路上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Roads bring many to their end.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.69,0:46:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每晚都有数百只小玳瑁被困在下水道\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hundreds get trapped in storm drains every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.63,0:46:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在陆地上的长途跋涉使它筋疲力尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Exhausted by the effort of travelling such a distance on land,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.05,0:46:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只小玳瑁很可能活不过今晚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this hatchling's chances of surviving the night are slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.57,0:47:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只玳瑁只是无数\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This turtle is one of the countless species
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.90,0:47:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无法适应城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that have been unable to adapt to the change
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.82,0:47:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,环境变化的物种之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}brought about by the urban environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.00,0:47:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有少数动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Only a small number of animals
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.30,0:47:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到了与人类共存的方法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have managed to find ways of living alongside us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.05,0:47:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每隔十年  就有英国面积大小的区域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And every 10 years, an area the size of Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.30,0:47:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被水泥森林吞噬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}disappears under a jungle of concrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.32,0:47:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但一切并非只能如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it doesn't have to be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.45,0:48:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道我们不能建造更加融合自然的城市吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Could it not be possible to build cities more in harmony with nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.73,0:48:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是这个环境的设计师\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}We are the designers of this enviroment.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.04,0:48:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否邀请野生动物回归城市  方式如何  都取决于我们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}How, and whether we decide to invite the wildlife back, is up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.47,0:48:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这棵树被吊到约三十层楼高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This tree is rising nearly 30 storeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.85,0:48:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它和其他近八百棵树一起被种下 旨在打造一座米兰的垂直森林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's one of almost 800 being planted to create a vertical forest in Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.27,0:48:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个数量的树木  相当于两公顷的森林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This number of living trees would normally fill two hectares of woodland,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.82,0:48:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可在这里  它们只占据了十分之一的面积\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but here, they occupy one-tenth of that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.37,0:48:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绿化建筑的外墙和屋顶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Greening the walls and roofs of our buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.54,0:48:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就能打造一座茂盛而广阔的栖息地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}could create a rich and extensive habitat,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.29,0:48:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要我们有心去做\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if we wanted it to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.58,0:49:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一座城市  正在大规模实践这个构想\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is one city where that idea is being applied on a major scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.34,0:49:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新加坡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.55,0:49:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座城市在四十五年里共种了两百万棵树\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two million trees have been planted here in the last 45 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.26,0:49:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今  它成为了世界上物种最丰富的城市\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This city is now richer in species than any other in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.53,0:49:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,构建自然城市的实践延伸至城市的每个角落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this practise extends to all parts of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.86,0:49:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城市中的航道被清理干净\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The waterways have been cleaned up,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.78,0:49:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,江獭们得以重新回归\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and smooth-coated otters are coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.17,0:49:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过  城市绿化最壮观的例子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But perhaps, the most spectacular example of city greening
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.75,0:49:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是这片超级树林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is this grove of super trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.38,0:50:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些四十五米高的金属建筑现在充满了生机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These 150 feet high metal structures are now full of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.52,0:50:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,分枝上种植了匍匐植物  蔓延生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Creepers have been planted to grow over the outermost branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.09,0:50:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是否就是我们未来的城市景观呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Is this a vision of our cities of the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.59,0:50:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许某天  我们会看到更多的野生动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The potential to see animals thriving within our cities
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.18,0:50:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在全世界的城市的里繁衍生息的景象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is achievable across the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.27,0:50:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今半数以上的人口生活在城市中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}More than half of us now live in an urban environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.11,0:50:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是否愿意打造美好的地球家园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Whether we choose to create a home for others too
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.04,0:50:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅是为了人类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is up to us.

